{"id": 7982, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "9-1-oxidation-and-reduction", "title": "19M.1.SL.TZ2.21", "topic_id": "9", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Which species contains nitrogen with the highest oxidation state?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">A. NO<sub>3</sub><sup>−</sup></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">B. NO<sub>2</sub><sup>−</sup></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">C. NO<sub>2</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">D. N<sub>2</sub>O</span></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>A</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>It is pleasing that 85 % of the candidates identified the species containing nitrogen with the highest oxidation state.</p>\n</div>"}